  "rationale": "<p>Multiplying the radicals: &radic;((p &minus; q)<sup>5</sup>) &middot; &radic;(p &minus; q) = &radic;((p &minus; q)<sup>6</sup>) = (p &minus; q)<sup>3</sup>. Expanding the binomial cube gives p<sup>3</sup> &minus; 3p<sup>2</sup>q + 3pq<sup>2</sup> &minus; q<sup>3</sup>. Choice A would result from (p &minus; q)<sup>2</sup>, which is the square root if the total power were 4 rather than 6.</p>",
